This HydraScalar tool suite was written by Kevin Skadron, derived from 
SimpleScalar 2.0e by Todd Austin.  Some HydraScalar material has been
contributed by Pritpal S. Ahuja.
 
The tool suite is currently maintained by Kevin Skadron.

All sources, unless otherwise indicated are Copyright (C) 1997-1999 by
Kevin Skadron

This source file is distributed "as is" in the hope that it will be
useful.  The tool set comes with no warranty, no support, and no
author or distributor accepts any responsibility for the consequences
of its use.

Any publications derived from HydraScalar must cite it appropriately:
  Kevin Skadron and Pritpal S. Ahuja.  "HydraScalar: A 
  Multipath-Capable Simulator."  Newsletter of the IEEE Technical
  Committee on Computer Architecture, Jan. 2001.
or
  P.S. Ahuja, K. Skadron, M. Martonosi, and D.W. Clark.  "Multipath
  Execution: Opportunities and Limits."  In Proceedings of the 1998
  International Conference on Supercomputing, pp.  101-08, July 1998.

